mg src=http://jenjer.50megs.com/faerie_dark.gif Width=100 Height=125></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Raid Rules</span><hr size=1> Rules Before the Raid:<br>
1. If you don't sign up, don't expect to walk on at the last minute and go.<br>
2. Persuant to #1, if you show up and whine about it, expect to never go even if you do sign up.<br>
3. Please make sure it is clear in your sign up post which character, by name, level, and class, is signing up for a raid. Without this information, the raid leaders cannot make effective preliminary raid plans.<br>
4. Be prepared to see the raid rescheduled by either time or date, cancelled, or even retargeted based on other data received by the raid leader during the sign up period. (For instance, we may find out that someone we know was already planning to raid XYZ so we will either reschedule, cancel, or retarget the raid.)<br>
5. Check back frequently on the raid thread in which you signed up in order to stay abreast of breaking news.<br>
6. Try to use just one post in each signup thread to minimize noise. If you think the raid leader missed something important then add a new post but if you are updating name, level, class, etc., please just edit your first post.<br>
7. It is up to the descretion of the raid leader who goes on the raid. Groups do not necessarily get formed in the order of who posted first. <br>
8. Be prepared with in game material. Bring spell reagents, food, water, arrows, throwing knives, etc....<br>
9. Be there early. If you are late, you may be told you have missed the raid.<br>
10.Leave your self interest at home. If you are worried about loot, experience or dying, then don't attend.<br>
<br>
Rules During the Raid:<br>
1. Always bring your resist gear to raids! You never know what boss mob will show up for you.<br>
2. Bring Peridots for your clerics! (Only tanks, pullers, clerics, and enchanters need symbols anyway except for mini-bosses.)<br>
3. Bring Peridots for Runes (if needed).<br>
4. No AoE unless/until raid leaders give permission.<br>
5. No pets until raid leaders give permission.<br>
6. Do NOT med against the wall in the portal area! (Plane of Hate)<br>
7. Do not push mobs through the wall in the portal area! (Plane of Hate)<br>
8. Casters do not nuke until mob is 50% or below. I don't want to play ping-pong with mobs.<br>
9. Before you zone into any Planar Zone /assist OFF.<br>
10. Do not attack until the main or secondary assist CALLS FOR ATTACK.<br>
11. Do not break mez!<br>
12. Snare anything that can be snared.<br>
13. Priests have first priority on Clarity 2, int casters next, and all others after. If your raid is dead, it doesn't matter what buffs you had.<br>
14. ONLY group leaders loot mobs. All gems go to loot dealer to be dealt out at the end of the raid, unless otherwise instructed by your raid leader.<br>
15. Do NOT loot an item REGARDLESS OF YOUR ROLL until the loot dealer says so.<br>
16. Shout channel is reserved to raid leaders. Please do not use this channel.<br>
17. OOC channel is for all other information. Please do not use OOC for idle chit-chat unless we are in a &quot;down time&quot; period. Snarers, slowers, debuffers, etc., all should have /OOC hotkeys that indicate actions that were just taken. i.e &quot;/OOC Mob ** %T ** has been SLOWED&quot; or &quot;/OOC SNARED %T&quot;, etc.<br>
18. NO RUNNING AROUND. Where you should be on any raid will be explained to you. Stay there!<br>
19. Have your assist key macro setup before the raid begins. Read the board or check with your group leader to determine who the main and secondary assists are. Hardcode your assist key to (a) assist the designated person, and (b) optionally, announce to your group who you are assisting. An example assist key macro might be two lines as follows:<br>
/assist Avergonis<br>
/groupsay Assisting Avergonis against %T<br>
20. Dont ask for certain types of mobs to be pulled. The pullers try to pull everything, but some stuff has to come before others due to physical location. If you have a special request that wouldnt normally be done, something like the broken golem in Fear, you need to have this info included in your signup so the raid leader can plan accordingly.<br>
<br>
<br>
SUGGESTIONS:<br>
1. /showspelleffects OFF<br>
2. Go to Options -&gt; Chat Filters and turn off other hits, other misses, damage shields, and anything else that you think you can live without. This will reduce the likelihood of going LD during the raid.<br>
3. Go to Options -&gt; Display and turn particle effects as low as you can stand (off preferably), turn off sky (none in Hate), etc., to minimize graphics load and reduce LDs during the raid.<br>
4. Certain classes (enchanters and clerics come to mind) will want to use discretion when selecting what effects to turn off. But do try to minimize your chances of going LD.<br>
5. If someone asks you for a buff, do not move around trying to target them. Instead just use the /target command (like &quot;/target Sorronn&quot;) to get them targeted. Then just stand up and buff.<br>
6. Use server side filtering to reduce packet count reaching your computer. To do this use the command /serverfilter ON<br>
7. Reserves. Sign up for reserves if you miss the main signup. Show up for the raid. There will always be someone very tardy or just plain not showing at all. However, if your on the reserves dont EXPECT to go, just hope.<br>
